  abstract = {AI Agents based on Large Language Models (LLMs) exhibit outstanding promise in tasks that call for cognitive abilities comparable to those of humans. But they usually have trouble solving complicated analytical data science problems that require multi-step, structured reasoning. We introduce Copilot Multi-Agentic System (Co-MAS), a system with multiple agents designed to handle complex analytical and reasoning tasks by using Finite State Machine (FSM) interactions. Co-MAS consists of a Planner Agent, Analyzer Agent, Validator Agent, Executer Agent, and Presenter Agent. Since these agents are horizontal in nature, Co-MAS can effectively address complex analytical and data science problems in any domain with a relevant context. With an average 12% increase in accuracy, Co-MAS significantly boosts standalone LLM performance in analytics and data science tasks. It accomplishes over 90% accuracy in a variety of machine learning tasks and an astounding 95.55% accuracy on the InfiAgent DA-bench dataset. Additionally, our solution maintains an average accuracy of 88% across top enterprise LLMs, demonstrating its LLM-agnostic nature.},
