  abstract = {This paper introduces Zrb, a novel framework designed to enhance code generation and task automation in software development. Addressing the challenges of manual errors and inefficiencies in the software development lifecycle, Zrb integrates concepts like Runner, Task, and Group to enable developers to run subsets of workflows with ease. Inspired by Apache Airflow's use of Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAGs), Zrb leverages these concepts for efficient task organization and execution. The framework supports various task types, including CmdTask for CLI commands and Python Task for Python-based scripts, providing flexibility and expressiveness. Furthermore, Zrb's ResourceMaker and Task Readiness features streamline resource generation and task execution processes, respectively. Practical applications in a production environment demonstrate Zrb's capability in running Prefect Server and Agent locally, generating and deploying Prefect Flows, executing DBT Commands, and monitoring deployments efficiently. The integration of Zrb into Github Actions highlights its adaptability in contemporary CI/CD pipelines. The framework significantly enhances team productivity by automating repetitive tasks, enabling quicker feedback loops, and seamlessly integrating with existing tools. Zrb emerges as a robust, versatile solution for workflow management and task automation, driving more agile and responsive software development processes.},
