  abstract = {Intelligent algorithms, especially clustering algorithms, have been widely used in the field of software analysis. Therefore, this study proposes the new financial management software (FMS) analysis model. First, this study reviews existing clustering algorithms and analyzes limitations of basic algorithms when processing large-scale financial data. The challenges of noise analysis are also reviewed. To this end, this study proposes a new clustering algorithm based on Gaussian mixture model. The core of this algorithm is to optimize parameter estimation by combining expectation maximization algorithm. At the same time, in order to improve clustering stability, a multi-feature model is introduced. This model can optimize the data selection and distance calculation paradigm in the clustering process. As for the usage of the clustering analysis, the main scenario is the software security. Focusing on the security, the enhanced model is proposed. This study also designs a security algorithm based on data stream analysis, which aims to ensure the privacy protection of the financial data during the clustering process. The experimental results show that the proposed model can effectively improve the data processing efficiency and security in financial management software. At the same time, the clustering test shows that the proposed model can stably analyze the software.},
